{{Infobox person | name = Frédéric Chatillon | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age |1968|2|15|df=yes}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | restingplace = | nationality = | religion = | ethnicity = | residence = | education = | alma mater = | occupation = | known for = communications adviser to [[Marine Le Pen]] | boards = | salary = | networth = | spouse = | parents = | children = | relations = | website = }}
'''Frédéric Chatillon''' (born 15 February 1968) is a French businessman, and communications adviser to [[Front National]] leader [[Marine Le Pen]].<ref name="ibtimes1">{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/france-right-wing-front-national-party-under-investigation-over-illegal-campaign-financing-1495747 |title=France: Right-wing Front National party under investigation over illegal campaign financing |website=Ibtimes.co.uk |date=2015-04-10 |accessdate=2016-04-06}}</ref>
Chatillon has been a "friend and confidant" of Le Pen since they were at law school together.<ref name="ibtimes1"/> As a student, he was president of [[Groupe Union Défense]], a far-right student group.
Juges Renaud Van Ruymbeke and Aude Buresi are investigating Chatillon for alleged "illegal financing" of the Front National.<ref name="ibtimes1"/>
French newspaper ''[[Le Monde]]'', as part of the [[Panama Papers]] investigation reported that Chatillon had used his company to set up an international network of shell companies and false invoices.<ref name="euronews1">{{cite web|url=http://www.euronews.com/2016/04/05/french-front-national-denies-implication-in-panama-papers/ |title=French Front National denies implication in Panama Papers &#124; euronews, world news |website=Euronews.com |date= |accessdate=2016-04-06}}</ref> On his Facebook page, Chatillon wrote, "obviously, the Front National has nothing to do with this private affair, neither directly or indirectly".<ref name="euronews1"/> The complex scheme is alleged to involve companies in complex system involving companies in Hong Kong, Singapore, Panama and the British Virgin Islands.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://sputniknews.com/europe/20160405/1037504395/panama-papers-marine-le-pen-close-circle-offshore-schemes.html |title=Marine Le Pen’s Close Circle Could Be Involved in Offshore Schemes |website=Sputniknews.com |date=2015-09-06 |accessdate=2016-04-06}}</ref>
The press allegations have been dismissed by the online news portal Atlantico <ref name="atlantico">{{cite web|url=http://www.atlantico.fr/decryptage/fn-et-panama-papers-pourauoi-affaire-chatillon-est-petard-mouille-gilles-gaetner-2666563.html|publisher=atlantico.fr|title=FN et Panama papers : pourquoi l'affaire Frédéric Chatillon n'est qu'un pétard mouillé &#124; Atlantico.fr|accessdate=2016-09-10}}</ref> as mere libels and politically oriented news.
==Personal life==
Frédéric Chatillon is separated<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rue89.nouvelobs.com/2014/06/09/lintervieweuse-ingenue-pen-amie-denfance-marine-a-lultradroite-252795 |title=L’intervieweuse ingénue de Le Pen : une amie d’enfance de Marine, issue de l’ultradroite - 9 juin 2014 - L'Obs |publisher=Rue89.nouvelobs.com |date= |accessdate=2017-04-01}}</ref> from Marie d’Herbais de Thun, born in 1971, friend of [[Marine Le Pen]], daughter of Pierre-Guillaume and Katherine d'Herbais de Thun, one of the Cendrine Blot-[[Jean-Marie Le Chevallier|Le Chevallier]] (born Chéreil de la Rivière) sisters.<ref>''Le Chevallier à découvert'', [[Jean-Pierre Thiollet]], Ed. Laurens, 1998, {{ISBN|2-911838-51-3}}, {{p.|33-34}}.</ref>
