{{Infobox person |name = Jan Å Berggren |image = JanBerggren.jpg |caption = Berggren in 2011 |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1946|06|12}} |birth_place = [[Malmö]], [[Sweden]] |nationality = [[Swedish people|Swedish]] {{flagicon|Sweden}} |alma_mater = [[Lund University]] |religion = |children = 2 | homepage = [http://www.Jakri.se/ www.Jakri.se] }}
'''Jan Å Berggren''' (born June 12, 1946) is a well known [[Swedish people|Swedish]] Real Estate <ref>http://www.jakri.se/</ref> developer who co-founded Jakri AB in 1983.<ref>http://gulasidorna.eniro.se/hitta:jakri+ab</ref> Berggren is best known for his pioneering <ref>http://www.enotes.com/topic/Jakriborg</ref> new urban village project, [[Jakriborg]] near Lund in [[South Sweden]] or [[Skåne County]]. Jan Berggren <ref>http://www.jakri.se/omraden.php</ref> and his younger brother and partner Krister built Jakri AB initially as a [[property]] [[Collective investment scheme|fund]]. In recent years the brothers have diversified their projects across [[Scandinavia]] <ref>http://www.planum.net/download/_js-pdf</ref> creating what is now one of South [[Sweden]]'s most successful family run [[Property]] Funds.<ref>http://www.a10.eu/magazine/issues/1/housing_jakriborg.html</ref>
==Jakriborg== Jan Berggren was interviewed by [[Sydsvenskan]] in 2011 in reference to [[Jakriborg]] which was ranked in a book publishing [[Sweden]]'s <ref>http://mudot.org/mudot2/MSW_instant.pdf</ref> 100 most remarkable sights', listing [[Jakriborg]] at number 2. Berggren's project has often been compared to [[Poundbury]] which was built by [[Prince Charles]] in England. Jan Berggren is regarded as one of the pioneers of [[Staffanstorp]] through the realization of his project Jakri together with his brother Krister (Hence '''Ja'''n and '''Kri'''ster ⁓ 'Jakri').<ref>http://www.sydsvenskan.se/omkretsen/staffanstorp/article1596402/60-ar-som-kommun.html</ref>
